                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00116 European War/12–644: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hayes</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-12-06T21:00:00+01:00"
                            >December 6, 1944—9 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received December 7—1:42 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3964. Your 3146, December 1, 8 p.m. While I shall gladly return to the charge in
                    an attempt to obtain an even more precise public undertaking from the Spanish
                    Government regarding denial of legal admission into Spain of Axis war criminals,
                    it seems to me that one of the most, if not the most practical step in this
                    regard would be to stop the Lufthansa service between Spain and Germany.
                    Department may wish to bring this matter to the attention of the Combined Chiefs
                    of Staff in connection with their consideration of the proposition referred to
                    in the Department’s 3087, November 23, 7 p.m.<note n="80" xml:id="d971fn80">
                        <ref target="frus1944v04#pg_454">Vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">iv</hi>, p.
                            454</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hayes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
